***

## Computer algorithm 
It's algorithm used to solve problems related to computer, simple one like sorting a groud of number to more complex one like data mining.
Now i will introduce you at this chapter to one of these problem which is sorting.

## Sorting 
Since i am programmer i will start by identifying what is the problem so i can solve it,
**Sorting** is the problem if representing numbers or alphabetic in the wrong order and your goal is to make them in the right order and i think it's the best problem to start to solve using a simple alogorithm.

## First algorithm: Bubble sort
it's a simple sorting algorithm that repeatedly steps through the list to be sorted, compares each pair of adjacent items and swaps them if they are in the wrong order. The pass through the list is repeated until no swaps are needed, which indicates that the list is sorted

<ol><strong>Oh, Lets have some fun</strong> 
<li>Get some playing cards or make some if you don't have one.</li>
<li>choose 8 different card that represent a number.</li>
<li>put them in the wrong order so we can start sorting them. </li>
<li>compares each pair of adjacent cards and swap them if they are in the wrong order.</li>
<li>go through this process over and over until they are in the right order.</li>
</ol>

[Check this out if you need some help](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bubble_sort#/media/File:Bubble-sort-example-300px.gif)

***

Now it's time to answer some questions and make this problem into a running program i will use <strong>Java</strong> to make my program, you can use any programming language you want but first lets start with the questions.

<ol><strong>Answer me</strong>
<li> What is the maximum number of operation you have to take so that our 8 numbers are sorted whatever the value of these number are </li>
<li> Do you think there is a better method to sort this numbers you use?. if yes tell me what they are. </li>
</ol>


***

### Code 

<code>

    public class App {
        public static void main(String[] args) {

            /// variables ///
            int[] sort_me = {6, 5, 3, 1, 8, 7, 2, 4};
            long startingTime, elapsedTime;

            /// let's print the array before sorting ///
            System.out.println("ARRAY BEFORE SORTING");
            for (int i = 0; i < sort_me.length; i++) {
                System.out.println("Array[" + i + "]= " + sort_me[i]);
            }

            System.out.println(); // let's make it look good

            startingTime = System.nanoTime();

            // Bubble sort algorithm ///

            for (int operation_number = 0; operation_number < sort_me.length - 1; operation_number++) {
                for (int element = 0; element< sort_me.length - 1; element++ ) {
                    if (sort_me[element] > sort_me[element + 1]) {

                        /// Swapping ///
                        int temporary = sort_me[element];
                        sort_me[element] = sort_me[element + 1];
                        sort_me[element + 1] = temporary;
                    }
                }
            }

            elapsedTime = System.nanoTime() - startingTime;


            /// let's print the array before sorting ///
            System.out.println("ARRAY AFTER SORTING");
            for (int i = 0; i < sort_me.length; i++) {
                System.out.println("Array[" + i + "]= " + sort_me[i]);
            }

            System.out.println("Time required : " +elapsedTime/6 + " Millisecond");





        }
    }

</code>
